10B beam scattered by 27Al foil (4.6 mg/cm2) to 3 deg
to 6 deg and refocused by a superconducting solenoid
Thick target inverse kinematics method
Beam flux measured by Faraday cup at the
entrance of the solenoid used together with the gold
elastic scattering data were used to get the
intensity of the secondary 10B beam, which was used
to determine the differential cross sections.
The following three targets in the target holder in
scattering chamber:
- 197Au foil (1.25 mg/cm2)
- Natural carbon foil (15 mg/cm2)
- Polyethylene plastic foil (100 um)
